        "title": "fix(commands): make /skill load workspace skills",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #88056.\n\n- Reload workspace skill commands for `/skill <name>` when the directive pass only supplied an empty placeholder list.\n- Preserve authoritative empty skill command lists when there is no loader, so filtered/no-skill turns still stay empty.\n- Move the `/stop` stale-message cutoff ahead of skill discovery and dispatch so queued stale skill commands cannot execute side-effecting skill tools.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD -- src/auto-reply/reply/commands-info.ts src/auto-reply/reply/commands-info.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply-inline-actions.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply-inline-actions.skip-when-config-empty.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/commands-info.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply-inline-actions.skip-when-config-empty.test.ts`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: `/skill <name> [input]` should invoke an available workspace skill command instead of returning `Unknown skill` when the directive pass provided an empty placeholder list.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw source checkout on the rebased PR branch using the repo Vitest wrapper.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/commands-info.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply-inline-actions.skip-when-config-empty.test.ts`\n\nEvidence after fix: Added regression coverage for named `/skill` reloading from an empty precomputed list, preserving authoritative empty lists without a loader, inline `/skill` workspace reload, and stale `/skill` messages being skipped before skill loading/tool dispatch.\n\nObserved result after fix: `Test Files 2 passed (2); Tests 38 passed (38)` and final autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings.\n\nWhat was not tested: Live chat provider end-to-end delivery was not exercised; this PR uses focused command-handler and inline-action tests for the implicated path.",
